The function waits for the thread to complete using the WaitForSingleObject function and then frees the allocated memory using the VirtualFreeEx function.

Finally, the function closes the handles to the process and the snapshot using the CloseHandle function.

The code is able to inject a DLL into a running process. This could be used to compromise the process or to gain control of the computer.
